            <title>SFA Soft Launches New Apps for Electrical, Pump Professionals</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	SFA Soft recently launched two new smartphone apps with more than 30 technical calculators for pumping machinery professionals and those who design and install electrical systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Electric Calcs and Pump Calcs, which are available for both Apple and Android devices, can be downloaded for free through the App Store and Google Play.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The Electric Calcs app calculators can determine the voltage drop in copper and aluminum wiring circuits, calculate real (true) power in three-phase transformers, and analyze transformer ratio data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The Pump Calcs app calculators can estimate the required brake horsepower for a given centrifugal pump application, determine efficiency of a motor-driven centrifugal pump, and calculate the average fluid velocity in a pipe when the flow rate is known.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Both free versions allow access to the basic technical calculators. There is a one-time cost of 99 cents for Electric Calcs and $1.99 for Pump Calcs to remove ads and enable the use of the more advanced calculators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	SFA Soft, which has been developing and managing database-driven technical websites since 2004, also plans to launch mobile-friendly websites for the electrical and pump calculations by the end of the year.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	For more information, contact &lt;a href="mailto:info@sfasoft.com"&gt;info@sfasoft.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/maintenance_and_reliability/~4/6pvnqsO50zY" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
            <a10:updated>2015-12-01T10:40:02-06:00</a10:updated>
