            <title>GE Introduces Cloud Service for Industrial Data, Analytics</title>
            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	GE recently announced plans to enter the cloud services market with a solution designed specifically for industrial data and analytics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Predix Cloud is a platform-as-a-service (PaaS) that captures and analyzes the unique volume, velocity and variety of machine data within a secure, industrial-strength cloud environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	The service is intended to drive the next phase of growth for the industrial Internet and enable developers to rapidly create, deploy and manage applications and services for industry.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	&amp;quot;A cloud built exclusively to capture and analyze machine data will make unforeseen problems and missed opportunities increasingly a complication of the past,&amp;quot; said Harel Kodesh, vice president at GE Software. &amp;quot;GE&amp;#39;s Predix Cloud will unlock an industrial app economy that delivers more value to machines, fleets and factories, and enable a thriving developer community to collaborate and rapidly deploy industrial applications in a highly protected environment.&amp;quot;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	Combining GE&amp;#39;s domain expertise in information technology and operational technology, Predix Cloud features advanced tools like asset connectivity, machine data support and industrial-grade security and compliance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	GE businesses will begin migrating their software and analytics to the Predix Cloud later in 2015. The service will be commercially available to customers and other industrial businesses in 2016.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
	For more information, visit &lt;a href="http://www.ge.com"&gt;www.ge.com&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;img src="http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/noria/reliableplant/tags/maintenance_and_reliability/~4/J0wNX0tW1A0" height="1" width="1" alt=""/&gt;</description>
