            <description>&lt;p&gt;
	In this 3-minute, 5-second video, Bill Barto of Life Cycle Engineering discusses the pitfalls of relying solely on the mean time between failures (MTBF) metric. See examples of systems not exhibiting a constant failure rate, which is assumed with the MTBF metric, and learn what other things you should consider when making the decision of how to devote your resources.&lt;/p&gt;
